#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga "
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Catumahārājasutta "
msgstr "37. The Four Great Kings (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.143, sc1
msgctxt "an3.37:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhamiyaṃ, bhikkhave, pakkhassa catunnaṃ mahārājānaṃ amaccā pārisajjā imaṃ lokaṃ anuvicaranti: "
msgstr "“On the eighth day of the fortnight, mendicants, the ministers and counselors of the Four Great Kings wander about the world, thinking: "

# NOTE: BB’s trans for patijararanti, which only seems to occur here, follows the comm, which I think is ridiculous, it means people are spending most of their time observing uposatha! Most likely it just means, be wakeful, probably staying up to meditate on the uposatha (like in Isaan?)
msgctxt "an3.37:1.2"
msgid "‘kacci bahū manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karontī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Hopefully most humans are paying due respect to their parents, ascetics and brahmins, honoring the elders in their families, observing the sabbath, staying awake, and making merit.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Cātuddasiṃ → cātuddisaṃ (bj) | cātuddasiyaṃ (s1-3) | cātuddasī (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.37:1.3"
msgid "Cātuddasiṃ, bhikkhave, pakkhassa catunnaṃ mahārājānaṃ puttā imaṃ lokaṃ anuvicaranti: "
msgstr "And on the fourteenth day of the fortnight, the sons of the Four Great Kings wander about the world, thinking: "

msgctxt "an3.37:1.4"
msgid "‘kacci bahū manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karontī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Hopefully most humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: mahārājāno → mahārājā (bj)
msgctxt "an3.37:1.5"
msgid "Tadahu, bhikkhave, uposathe pannarase cattāro mahārājāno sāmaññeva imaṃ lokaṃ anuvicaranti: "
msgstr "And on the fifteenth day sabbath, the Four Great Kings themselves wander about the world, thinking: "

msgctxt "an3.37:1.6"
msgid "‘kacci bahū manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karontī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Hopefully most humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.37:2.1"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, appakā honti manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karonti. "
msgstr "If only a few humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit, "

#. VAR: mahārājāno → mahārājā (bj)
#. VAR: sudhammāya sabhāya → sudhammāyaṃ sabhāyaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.37:2.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, cattāro mahārājāno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sudhammāya sabhāya sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ārocenti: "
msgstr "then the Four Great Kings address the gods of the Thirty-Three, seated together in the Hall of Justice: "

msgctxt "an3.37:2.3"
msgid "‘appakā kho, mārisā, manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karontī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Only a few humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit.’ "

msgctxt "an3.37:2.4"
msgid "Tena kho, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā anattamanā honti: "
msgstr "Then the gods of the Thirty-Three are disappointed, thinking, "

#. VAR: asurakāyā’ti → asurā kāyāti (bj)
msgctxt "an3.37:2.5"
msgid "‘dibbā vata, bho, kāyā parihāyissanti, paripūrissanti asurakāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The heavenly hosts will dwindle, while the demon hosts will swell!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.37:3.1"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, bahū honti manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karonti. "
msgstr "But if many humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit, "

msgctxt "an3.37:3.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, cattāro mahārājāno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sudhammāya sabhāya sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ārocenti: "
msgstr "then the Four Great Kings address the gods of the Thirty-Three, seated together in the Hall of Justice: "

msgctxt "an3.37:3.3"
msgid "‘bahū kho, mārisā, manussā manussesu matteyyā petteyyā sāmaññā brahmaññā kule jeṭṭhāpacāyino uposathaṃ upavasanti paṭijāgaronti puññāni karontī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Many humans are paying due respect to their parents … and making merit.’ "

msgctxt "an3.37:3.4"
msgid "Tena, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā attamanā honti: "
msgstr "Then the gods of the Thirty-Three are pleased, thinking, "

#. VAR: asurakāyā’ti → asurā kāyāti (bj)
msgctxt "an3.37:3.5"
msgid "‘dibbā vata bho kāyā paripūrissanti, parihāyissanti asurakāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The heavenly hosts will swell, while the demon hosts will dwindle!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.37:4.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Once upon a time, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the Thirty-Three, recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.144, sc5
#. VAR: Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ → cātuddasī pañcadasī (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.37:5.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: aṭṭhamī → aṭṭhamiṃ (si)
msgctxt "an3.37:5.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī; "
msgstr "would observe the sabbath "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:5.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca, "
msgstr "complete in all eight factors, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:5.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:5.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya, "
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yopissa → yopassa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.37:5.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti. "
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an3.37:6.1"
msgid "Sā kho panesā, bhikkhave, sakkena devānamindena gāthā duggītā na sugītā dubbhāsitā na subhāsitā. "
msgstr "But that verse was poorly sung by Sakka, lord of gods, not well sung; poorly spoken, not well spoken. "

msgctxt "an3.37:6.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.37:6.3"
msgid "Sakko hi, bhikkhave, devānamindo avītarāgo avītadoso avītamoho. "
msgstr "Sakka, lord of gods, is not free of greed, hate, and delusion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: tassa kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno → tassa kho etaṃ bhikkhuno (s1-3) | tassa kho evaṃ bhikkhave bhikkhuno (mr)
msgctxt "an3.37:7.1"
msgid "Yo ca kho so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā brahmacariyo katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto, tassa kho etaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kallaṃ vacanāya: "
msgstr "But for a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is rightly freed through enlightenment—it is appropriate to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.37:8.1"
msgid "‘Cātuddasiṃ pañcadasiṃ, "
msgstr "‘Whoever wants to be like me "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:8.2"
msgid "yā ca pakkhassa aṭṭhamī; "
msgstr "would observe the sabbath, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:8.3"
msgid "Pāṭihāriyapakkhañca, "
msgstr "complete in all eight factors, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:8.4"
msgid "aṭṭhaṅgasusamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "on the fourteenth and the fifteenth days, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:8.5"
msgid "Uposathaṃ upavaseyya, "
msgstr "and the eighth day of the fortnight, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.37:8.6"
msgid "yopissa mādiso naro’ti. "
msgstr "as well as on the fortnightly special displays.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.37:9.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an3.37:9.2"
msgid "So hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vītarāgo vītadoso vītamoho”ti. "
msgstr "Because that mendicant is free of greed, hate, and delusion.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.37:9.3"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
